      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a constitutional principle that has been essential in safeguarding civil rights and individual liberties. It ensures that laws and government actions do not infringe upon fundamental rights, such as privacy, freedom of speech, and equal protection under the law. By interpreting the Due Process Clause of the 14th Amendment, the Supreme Court has struck down laws that discriminate against marginalized groups, thereby promoting a more just and inclusive society. This judicial approach has been crucial in advancing civil rights, from desegregation to same-sex marriage, and continues to protect individual freedoms against unjust government interference.",
